1.Project Title  
Mini Project 8: Unit Conversion System using Python  
Unit Conversion System using Python  
2. Problem Statement  
In daily life, people often need to convert units such as length, temperature, and weight. 
Manual conversion is time-consuming and error-prone. Hence, there is a need for an 
automated system that performs accurate and quick unit conversions.  
3. Objective  
.To develop a simple unit conversion program.    
.To convert values between different measurement units  
.To reduce manual calculation errors.  
.To provide user-friendly interaction.  
4. Tools Used  
a. Python 3  
b. VS Code / IDLE  
5. Description  
The Unit Conversion System is a Python-based application that converts values from one unit to 
another. The system takes user input, performs calculations using formulas, and displays the result 
instantly.  
It supports:  
• Length conversion (meters ↔ kilometers)   
• Temperature conversion (Celsius ↔ Fahrenheit)   
• Weight conversion (kg ↔ grams)   
6. Algorithm  
1. Start the program  
2. Display menu (Length, Temperature, Weight)  
3. Get user choice  
4. Input value  
5. Perform conversion using formula  
6. Display result  
7. Stop the program    
7. Result  
The program successfully converts units such as length, temperature, and weight accurately 
based on user input.  
8. Conclusion  
The Unit Conversion System simplifies everyday calculations by providing quick and 
accurate conversions. It is user-friendly and reduces human errors, making it useful for 
students and professionals.  
